#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"layout: post\n"
"title: Contributing to Quarkus for the first time\n"
"date: 2020-10-05\n"
"tags: contribution hacktoberfest\n"
"synopsis: Hacktoberfest has begun and you wonder how to contribute to your "
"favorite framework? We will try to give you some answers in this article.\n"
"author: lmathieu\n"
"---\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Hacktoberfest has begun and Quarkus, as a lot of other Open Source projects, "
"is a perfect place to make your contributions to fulfill this 4 PR challenge "
"in meaningful way."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Today, Monday, at 6:30pm CEST, I will make a live stream on _How to "
"contribute to Quarkus for the first time_ on "
"link:https://quarkus.io/insights/[Quarkus Insights],"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:16
msgid ""
"I will use the advice in the blog below in practice and create contributions "
"live.  If it's of interest to you, come and join us, we'll answer as much "
"question as we can, the details are in this "
"link:https://twitter.com/QuarkusIO/status/1311959006366363648[tweet]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Quarkus has a very welcoming community, we welcome contributions from "
"everybody, and try to make our best to help people making contributions even "
"if they are not familiar with it.  So don't be shy and reach out to us if "
"you want to contribute!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "How I got started "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:22
msgid ""
"In this article, I will try to give you some tips to help you create your "
"first contribution to Quarkus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:24
msgid ""
"I was a new contributor myself some times ago you may wonder how I have "
"started?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:26
msgid "With small contributions: bugfixes and documentations of course!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:31
msgid ""
"Then I had the opportunity to meet Quarkus core members Emmanuel Bernard and "
"Clement Escoffier at Devoxx France, and we had a long discussion on MongoDB "
"followed by some email exchanges.  After this, I helped to test the Mongo "
"Client extension (authored by Clément Escoffier). + All this leads to the "
"creation of the MongoDB with Panache extension, a huge work of design, "
"coding and re-coding, documentation, ...  Creating this extension took me "
"several weeks (even if the core development was done in a few days) so if "
"you plan to make an extension, be prepared (the review itself took several "
"weeks with more than 250 github comments)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:33
msgid ""
"This was challenging, exciting, enriching, ... but if you plan to do the "
"same be prepared to a long journey."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:35
msgid "OK, now let's see how to make your first contribution to Quarkus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting things up"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Before being able to contribute, you must fork the "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus[Quarkus repository] and build it "
"on you local computer, even if you plan to contribute in an other area of "
"Quarkus (more information on this later), you must be able to build the main "
"Quarkus repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:42
msgid ""
"Clone the repository : `git clone "
"https://github.com/<your-fork-repo>/quarkus.git` then build Quarkus via `mvn "
"clean install -Dquickly`.  The Maven command will launch a minimal build of "
"Quarkus and install the dependencies locally."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:44
msgid ""
"If it didn't work follow the "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#setup[CONTRIBUTING "
"- Setup] page to setup your environment, anyway at some point you may need "
"to read this page!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:47
msgid ""
"If you're new to Quarkus: read the guides in the "
"link:https://quarkus.io/get-started[getting started page], you can skip the "
"native and reactive ones if you don't plan to contribute on these areas, and "
"as a new contributor I'll advise you to avoid them!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:49
msgid ""
"You can read the "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md[CONTRIBUTING] "
"page for general guidelines, if you don't understand everything don't panic "
";), or you can refer to it if needed as it can be hard to read for "
"newcomers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:51
msgid ""
"Then, the hardest part will begin, you will need to find what you plan to do "
"as a contributor, you can make contributions in the following areas:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:53
msgid "documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:54
msgid "code : core, extension, devtools"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:55
msgid "integration test"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:56
msgid "quickstart"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:57
msgid "website"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:60
msgid ""
"Or just tell us your story with Quarkus, we love to hear user stories, and "
"have a "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/ADOPTERS.md[dedicated "
"page], and blog category "
"link:https://quarkus.io/blog/tag/user-story[#user-story] for them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:64
msgid ""
"We make our best to offer "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22good+first+issue%22[good "
"first issue], and you can ask as many questions as you want (none are stupid "
"questions) in our Zulip "
"link:https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187038-dev[dev] "
"channel. + We even setup a dedicated channel for Hacktoberfest: "
"link:https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/243144-hackathon[hackaton]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working on something"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:68
msgid ""
"When you're decided to work on something, you can find help on Zulip or "
"Github by pinging area "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/MAINTAINERS.adoc[maintainers]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:70
msgid ""
"If there is an issue already opened, ask that someone assign it to you (you "
"can add a comment for this on the issue)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:72
msgid ""
"If you plan to work on new stuff, ask on Zulip or the "
"link:https://groups.google.com/d/forum/quarkus-dev[mailing list] before "
"starting for all community to be aware of your plan."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:75
msgid ""
"If you want to create a new extension, congratulation! But you should "
"definitely ask on the mailing list plus create an "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/new?assignees=&labels=kind%2Fextension-proposal&template=extension_proposal.md&title=[extension "
"proposal] on github.  Extension contribution is a long process with a design "
"phase, and a discussion phase prior to any implementation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:77
msgid ""
"As a newcomer, better to make small contributions first, remember my "
"personal story on the introduction ..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tips on contributing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:81
msgid ""
"Now it is time to give you some tips to facilitate your first contribution "
"based on the different contribution type you can do."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Quarkus documentation is based on guides that are located inside the "
"`docs/src/main/asciidoc` of the Quarkus repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:87
msgid ""
"There is a separate Asciidoc file per guide. The name of the guide is the "
"last part of the doc URL so they are easy to find."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:89
msgid ""
"After any documentation contribution, always build the guide via `mvn clean "
"package` and test them!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:91
msgid ""
"The guides are generated as HTML so you can open them in a browser, be "
"careful to always test the links as it's the most common cause of "
"documentation issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Integration Test"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:95
msgid ""
"Quarkus integration tests are in the `integration-tests` directory of the "
"Quarkus main repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:97
msgid ""
"There should be at least one test by extension plus the `main` one that "
"tests together multiple extensions that are common on rest services: JAX-RS, "
"Health, JPA, ..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:101
msgid ""
"When you update a test, it's better to launch it on both JVM mode using `mvn "
"clean test` and native mode using `mvn clean integration-test "
"-Pnative-image` (the native profile can have a different name, check the "
"pom.xml if needed).  If you didn't setup native image compilation in your "
"computer, you can let the CI run it for you in native."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:103
msgid ""
"If you plan to add a new integration test, ask for some advice as there will "
"be some extra steps to take to configure the CI."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "Code"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:108
msgid ""
"The code is split into multiple parts, I didn't contribute to all of them so "
"I will only introduce the one I know the best, but they are also the easiest "
"one to contribute so it should be enough to start with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:110
msgid "You will find the following areas:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*core*: this is the core runtime and deployment modules of Quarkus. Ask for "
"help if you want to contribute in it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "*devtools*: where the Maven and Gradle plugins lies.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*bom*: where all libraries are managed. Be sure to build all the Quarkus "
"relevant tests after updating a library.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:115
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*extension*: where all the extensions lies. An extension is an integration "
"of a third party library or framework into Quarkus.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:118
msgid ""
"Most contributions are done inside the extensions, at least for new "
"contributors, as the other area are harder to work on.  It is best to read "
"the link:https://quarkus.io/guides/building-my-first-extension[Building my "
"first extension] guide to have an overview of how extensions works."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:120
msgid "Extensions are split into two parts (and an optional third one):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*deployment*: code executed at build time. It should contain a build "
"processor that execute build steps and generate build items.\n"
"If you need to contribute to the deployment part of an extension be sure to "
"read the link:https://quarkus.io/guides/writing-extensions[extension author "
"guide] and to understand the extension philosophy section.\n"
"Personally I love this old presentation "
"link:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=za5CSBX-UME[Quarkus and GraalVM: "
"booting Hibernate at supersonic speed, subatomic size] by Sanne Grinovero "
"that explains how Hibernate is integrated inside Quarkus, but there should "
"be other contents that may explain the extension design.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*spi*: optional - allow to share some build items with some other extension "
"deployment modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*runtime*: code executed at runtime. It includes the extension "
"configuration, a recorder (records runtime deployment build steps to re-do "
"them when you application starts),\n"
"the user API if any, and all the code that allow to start the "
"library/framework.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:129
msgid ""
"Each extension should have its integration test, if not, check if the "
"extension is tested inside the `main` one. Be sure to launch the test before "
"commmiting your changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:131
msgid ""
"Each extension has its guide, if you add a new functionality, document it "
"there!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:133
msgid ""
"Before commiting, you must be sure that your code passes the formatting "
"style and obey to the enforcer rules. The better way to do this is to "
"install the extension locally via ̀`mvn clean install`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quickstart"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:137
msgid ""
"The Quickstarts are located inside a "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus-quickstarts[separate repo], that "
"has its own "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus-quickstarts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md[contributing "
"guidelines]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:139
msgid "Again, you need to fork it and work on your own fork."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:141
msgid ""
"Each extension should have its own quickstart, the link of the quickstart "
"should be on the extension guide (but it's not always the case)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:143
msgid ""
"The quickstart must reflect as much as possible the code described inside "
"the extension guide, so don't contribute something inside it that didn't "
"reflect the guide."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:145
msgid "As always, before pushing your changes: test and install it locally!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Website"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:149
msgid ""
"The website is located in a "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkusio.github.io[separate repo], that "
"has its own "
"link:https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkusio.github.io/blob/develop/CONTRIBUTING.md[contributing "
"guidelines]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:151
msgid ""
"I only contributed once to it and I didn't remember any special tips that "
"again, test and install it locally!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:153
msgid ""
"The guides are in the main Quarkus repo so don't try to update one of them "
"inside the website repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a PR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:157
msgid ""
"Push to your fork after having reviewed locally your changes, tested them "
"and installed the updated component locally."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:161
msgid ""
"Always wait for the github action on your own fork to end before opening a "
"PR, a full CI run took hours so better to be sure it passes before making it "
"run on the Quarkus repo. + There is a "
"link:https://youtu.be/egqbx-Q-Cbg[small video] that explain our CI and how "
"to activate it in your fork."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:163
msgid "Then, create a PR, and the review process will start ;)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:165
msgid ""
"There is a bot that tags the PRs and ping the maintainers of the area, if it "
"didn't tagged yours, you can wait a few hours for someone to notice it, or "
"ping someone directly or reach out on Zulip or the mailing list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wrapup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:169
msgid "This is a long post, and I hope it'll help you contributing to Quarkus!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:171
msgid ""
"As I repeat it during this post: *start small, test everything, ask for "
"help*. These are my best advices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-10-05-contributing-for-the-first-time.adoc:174
msgid ""
"Today, Monday, at 6:30pm CEST, I will make a live stream on _How to "
"contribute to Quarkus for the first time_ on "
"link:https://quarkus.io/insights/[Quarkus Insights], I will take these "
"advices in practice and create contributions in live.  If it's of interest "
"to you, come and join us, we'll answer as much question as we can, the "
"details are in this "
"link:https://twitter.com/QuarkusIO/status/1311959006366363648[tweet]."
msgstr ""
